---
import BaseHead from "../../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../../consts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
      description="About the blog author and the purpose of this blog."
      lang="en"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header lang="en" />
    <main>
      <article>
        <h1>About</h1>

        <h2>About the Author</h2>
        <p>
          Hello! I'm a backend developer with hands-on experience building
          and operating services based on Spring Boot, AWS, and Kubernetes.
          Recently, I've been focusing on AI coding agents and DevOps
          automation. I run this blog to share practical insights gained
          from real-world projects.
        </p>

        <h2>Blog Mission</h2>
        <p>
          This blog provides practical, hands-on technical content. Rather
          than simple theory summaries, it delivers project-ready architectures,
          code examples, and lessons learned from trial and error.
        </p>

        <h2>Main Topics</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Backend Development</strong> — Framework usage, API design,
            error handling, and production-ready patterns
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Infrastructure & DevOps</strong> — Cloud, container
            orchestration, CI/CD, IaC, and monitoring
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>AI Development Tools</strong> — AI coding agent workflows
            and automation
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Security</strong> — Authentication/authorization and web
            security policies in practice
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Value for Readers</h2>
        <p>
          Every article is written with the question "Can I apply this right
          now?" in mind. We provide the practical context that official docs
          alone cannot convey — configuration pitfalls, reasoning behind design
          choices, and actionable takeaways.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For feedback or inquiries about the blog content, please visit the
          <a href="/en/contact">Contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer lang="en" />
  </body>
</html>
